                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#9rb">Fol. 9rb</locus>: Ownership note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in the main hand. The name of the owner (written over erasure, ʾabba ʿAbiyä ʾƎgziʾ?) has been washed out.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#9va">Fol. 9va</locus>-vb: List of witnesses for the land ownership in Mǝkwǝʿat Märet.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 9va: ኆልቈ፡ ምስክር፡ ዘምኵዓት። ተክለ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ወድ፡ በዓተይ፡ ሹም፡ ተክለ፡ ኢየሱስ። ...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           It lists witnesses involved in a dispute over land ownership (s. Additio 4). The scribe Kiros mentions himself at the end of the note.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#10ra">Fol. 10ra</locus>-va: ʾƎsäggǝd läki wä-ʾǝweddǝsäki ... "I worship Thee ...".<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#171vb">Fol. 171vb</locus>: Record concerning land donation. <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 171vb: በከመ፡ ወሐበት፡ ቅድመ፡ ጀን፡ መንግሣ። በመዋእለ፡ መንግሥተ፡ አቡሐ፡ ዳዊት፡ ብሒላ፡ ምኩአት፡ መሬት፡ ይኩን፡ ለተዘካረ፡ አቡነ፡ አብየ፡ እግዚእ፡ ...</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is written in a 17th-cent. (?) crude hand. The donor ʾAmätä ʾAb refers to her land donation to the church, which is given similarly to the land of Mǝkuʾat Märet given for the commemoration of ʾabunä ʾAbǝyä ʾƎgziʾ by Queen(?) Ğän Mängǝśa during the reign of her father Dawit (II).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Endleaves fols. 1, 172, 174 are fragments of an old 15th-cent. (?) Synaxarion, containing parts of commemorative notices for:&#xD;
 22 and 23 Ḫǝdar (Cosmas and Damian, Cornelius); 8 Taḫśaś (Esi and Thecla, Samuel); 7 and 8 Taḫśaś (Samuel, Barbara and Juliana, Mathew). &#xD;
- The first strophe of Text I-1 is repeated in the upper margin of fol. 13v, in hand a.&#xD;
- Titles of most of the miracles of St Mary (Text I-4a) are written in the upper margin of the miracle's incipit page, in red.&#xD;
- Corrections are written over erasures: e.g., fols. 13rab, 33rb, 48ra, 69rb, 90va, 93rb, 149rb, 157va, 165va, 171rb.&#xD;
- A note has been erased from fol. 9rb, below Additio 1.&#xD;
- Several lines have been erased from fol. 77rb.&#xD;
- Sketches for ornamental bands on fols. 21va, 28rb, 34va, 49ra; probably in hand a.&#xD;
- Spaces for rubricated names of the donor are left unfilled throughout Text I-4b.&#xD;
- Crude drawings on fol. 173rv.</item>
                     </list>
